<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8561> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8561" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 734" ;
	dprr:hasID 8561 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2795> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2795" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent with instructions from the Senate to assist Paullus in organizing Macedonia (Liv. 45.17.2-3, and 29-31). Claudius and Domitius went to Achaea to summon the Achaean leaders to Rome in person (Liv. 45.31.9-11; cf. Polyb. 30.13.8-11), and Fabius went to Lesbos to destroy Antissa and incorporate it with Methymna (Liv. 45.31.14)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2795 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2783> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2783" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued in Gaul (Liv. 45.17.2), until his appointment as Legate (see below), when the Consul Aelius succeeded to his province (Liv. 45.17.2 and 5-6)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2783 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2730> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2730" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 44.17.4, and 19.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 50f., 123, 460f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Aemilius, Cic. Div. 1.103; 2.83; Elog., CIL 1\n     .1, p. 194- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.71 and 81; CIL 1(2).2.763b; Val. Max. 1.5.3; 7.5.3; Plut. Aem. 10.1-3. Aemilius received charge of the war with Perseus of Macedon, whom he crushed at Pydna and later captured (Polyb. 29.14-18, and 20.1-4; Cic. Att. 4.13.2; Liv. 44.21.1-3, 22.16, and 33-46; 45.4.2-7, and 7-8; Plut. Aem. 12-27; cf. Cic. ND 2.6; Verr. 2.1.55; Tusc. 5.118; Diod. 30.22-23; Vell. 1.9; Val. Max. 1.8.1; 5.1.8; 8.11.1; Frontin. Str. 2.3.20; Iustin. 33.1-2; Flor. 1.28.7-12; Dio fr. 67; Eutrop. 4.6-7; Oros. 4.20.39; Zon. 9.23). He then spent some time in touring Greece (Polyb. 30.10.1-6; Liv. 45.27-28; Plut. Aem. 28.1-2; cf. CIL 1(2).2.622-ILS 8884). Licinius' province was Italy, with charge of levies and supplies for the Macedonian war (Liv. 44.17.10, 19.5, 21.11, and 22.5). After Pydna he dismissed his levies (Liv. 45.1-2), and later went to Gaul (45.12.9-12)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2730 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2660> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2660" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under his brother in Macedonia, commanding the right wing at Callinicus (Liv. 42.58.12)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2660 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2611> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2611" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Placed, along with Cn. Sicinius, in charge of freeing the Statelliates enslaved by M. Popillius (Liv. 42.21.2-5, and 22.4-5), but postponed the trial of Popillius himself to let him escape punishment (42.22.7-8). Aided in military preparations for the war with Perseus of Macedon (42.27.1-3 and 5; FOR 1.72-74, and 202, fr. 180; cf. Fest. 266 L)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2611 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2610> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2610" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 42.9.8 Provinces and armies 42.10.13-14, and 18.2 and 6-7." ;
	dprr:hasID 2610 .
